pr_title: Data Source Adapter for Google Sheets
pr_body:
### Final report: GSoC '22
- Student: Anh Tran
- Organization: [Polypheny](https://polypheny.org/)
- Mentors: [David](https://github.com/datomo), [Marc](https://github.com/hennlo)
- Project: [Project proposal](https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/programs/2022/projects/fmDSiX3x)

---
### Project

I have written an adapter to query tables from the Google Sheets. For each google sheet URL, this adapter looks into its sheets and creates a table for each of them with the respective column names and data. I used the [Google Sheet Java Api](https://developers.google.com/sheets/api/quickstart/java) to develop the interface between Polypheny and Google Sheets. 

The package is mostly done, with the usage instructions and potential improvements / future changes all put into the README.md file in the google-sheet-adapter. 

This contribution also includes the smaller PR: [monitoring threads](https://github.com/polypheny/Polypheny-DB/pull/410/files)

---

Thank you so much for this opportunity, I've learned a lot and working with everyone has been a pleasure.
